From: Guoqing Jiang <Guoqing.Jiang@windriver.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Jun 2011 11:41:18 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 15/20] TI816x nand: add nand support in Kconfig

Add nand support for 816x.

This patch is based on below commit from arago git tree.
git://arago-project.org/git/projects/linux-omap3.git
b70cd6 ti816x: Adding NAND support

Signed-off-by: Mansoor Ahamed <mansoor.ahamed@ti.com>
[This one is picked from the original commit to compatible
with wrlinux tree]
Integrated-by: Guoqing Jiang <Guoqing.Jiang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mtd/nand/Kconfig |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mtd/nand/Kconfig b/drivers/mtd/nand/Kconfig
index f4594af..b32d3e0 100644
--- a/drivers/mtd/nand/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/mtd/nand/Kconfig
@@ -74,7 +74,7 @@ config MTD_NAND_AMS_DELTA
 
 config MTD_NAND_OMAP2
 	tristate "NAND Flash device on OMAP2 and OMAP3"
-	depends on ARM && MTD_NAND && (ARCH_OMAP2 || ARCH_OMAP3)
+	depends on ARM && MTD_NAND && (ARCH_OMAP2 || ARCH_OMAP3 || ARCH_TI816X)
 	help
           Support for NAND flash on Texas Instruments OMAP2 and OMAP3 platforms.
 
